# SQLite Migration, Dynamic Scheduling, and Location Tracking Plan

This plan outlines the steps to resolve the PostgreSQL connection failures (`ECONNREFUSED`), fix tracking parameter parsing errors, and implement dynamic timeslot scheduling and location/address capturing.

---

## User Review Required

### 1. Database Migration to SQLite
> [!IMPORTANT]
> **Why we are switching to SQLite:**
> Currently, the backend attempts to connect to PostgreSQL at `localhost:5432` but fails because no PostgreSQL service is running on the machine (`ECONNREFUSED`).
> To provide a zero-config, immediate setup that runs anywhere without requiring external database software, we will switch Prisma to use **SQLite** with a local file database (`dev.db`). 
>
> We will run a database push (`npx prisma db push`) to build the SQLite database and seed it with basic initial data so the application is fully functional.

### 2. Time-Slot Scheduling & Conflict Resolution
> [!TIP]
> **Dynamic Slot Allocation:**
> 1. We will define 5 standard daily timeslots.
> 2. The backend will expose a `GET /orders/available-slots?date=YYYY-MM-DD` endpoint.
> 3. It will scan the database for existing orders on the selected date. If a timeslot is already booked, it will be marked as unavailable (`available: false`) to avoid conflicts.
> 4. The frontend will dynamically fetch and disable booked slots based on the chosen date.

